  <refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis format="linespecific">#include &lt;openssl/dsa.h&gt;</synopsis>
<synopsis format="linespecific">int DSA_size(const DSA *dsa);</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection xml:id="sources.openssl.doc.crypto.DSA_size.pod:DESCRIPTION"><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      This function returns the size of an ASN.1 encoded DSA signature in
      bytes. It can be used to determine how much memory must be allocated
      for a DSA signature.
    </para>
    <para>
      <emphasis role="bold">dsa-&gt;q</emphasis> must not be <emphasis role="bold">NULL</emphasis>.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection xml:id="sources.openssl.doc.crypto.DSA_size.pod:RETURN_VALUE"><title>RETURN VALUE</title>
    <para>
      The size in bytes.
    </para>
  </refsection>
